{"change_summary":"No additional code edits were required in this apply-fixes round. The completion-round-17 review approved the milestone task-run lineage implementation without amendments, so I left the code unchanged and carried forward the validated state from the latest reviewed build.","outstanding_risks":["Milestone mutations still span separate lineage, snapshot, and journal files without a cross-file transaction; milestone-scoped locking and replay-safe updates mitigate this, but a crash between file writes can still leave snapshot or journal state temporarily behind `task-runs.ndjson` until the same operation is replayed or state is reconciled from lineage.","Malformed or manually edited lineage can still contain multiple simultaneous runless open attempts for the same bead/project; the normal start path now prevents stale legacy-open contradictions for new named retries, but deterministic finalization of already-corrupt data still depends on repair or richer caller metadata."],"steps":[{"description":"Reviewed the approved completion-round-17 validation output and confirmed there were no follow-up fixes or amendments to apply.","order":0,"status":"completed"},{"description":"Left the existing milestone task-run lineage implementation unchanged because the approved review found no remaining defects requiring code changes.","order":1,"status":"completed"},{"description":"Carried forward the approved validation evidence for formatting, milestone_record tests, and clippy from the latest reviewed implementation.","order":2,"status":"completed"}],"validation_evidence":["Approved review evidence confirms `cargo fmt --all --check` passes with no formatting issues.","Approved review evidence confirms `cargo test --lib contexts::milestone_record` passes with 103 tests.","Approved review evidence confirms `cargo clippy -- -D warnings` passes cleanly."]}